    {
      "label": "Transcript",
      "value": "Dean Hall Cooper River 21st June 1866- Dear Sir I am willing to allow the mill the following hands, but of course expect both saws to run with reduced numbers if it is impossible to procure the full amount, viz: One Sawyer to each Saw 2 One CrossCut Sawyer 1 Two HdBrock men to each carriage 4 One behind each saw to wedge out lumber and help turn logs 2 One to haul up logs 1 One behind each saw [illegible] runoff lumber 2 Two at Cross-cut Saw 2 Two to remove lumber on cart 2 One to assist in front and keep saw dust [illegible] 1 One Engineer 1 Two to fire and furnish [illegible] 2 Total 20 --wish you to have the whistle blown at the following hours and in the following manner: viz At 5.30 AM 2 blows 1st Call to work- 6 A.M. 1 long blow 2 call to work 12 PM 3 blows knock off for dinner- 12.50 PM 2 blows 1st Call to work [End Page 1] 1P.M. the long blow 2nd Call to work 6 P.M. 3 blows call to stop work. I wish that you would explain the calls to the workmen and let them understand that they must be at their places at each second call or a deduction will be made from their pay- I enclose a sample of ticket which I wish given to each of the hands- weekly or oftener if they should need it showing the amnt. of time they have made and have to be paid for. Please explain that they can draw provisions on these certificates at any time during the month and that on pay day they will be paid according to their tickets the amounts undrawn- I wish you in addition to keep a time book which ought of course to accord with the tickets issued- I notice every now and then some one or two of the hands smoking in the mill this I wish you to put a stop to, for with all the saw dust lightwood &c around the mill there is great danger of fire from smoking-I wish that you would arrange with one of the hands as fireman on an increase of wages [End Page 2] and require him to have steam up in the morning- The arrangement I wish made with the colored hands is as follows. fireman- 80 cts pr day- that is $21.60 pr mo- Hands 68 cts pr day- that is $18.36 pr mo- The firemen and hands to be able to draw supplies on the tickets of work as mentioned above. The white hands to be paid $1.00 pr diem I will let them have provisions also on a/c of wages- Very Respt &c T. B. Ferguson Mr W W Smitts Miller Dean Hall Saw Mill [End Page 3]"
    },
